Operational Front	"2093 Philadelphia Pike #3129"	Identified Envest Research Inc. in Claymont, DE; found the NY-to-DE jurisdictional pivot.
IP Holding Shell	"1309 Coffeen Ave" "MTA Global"	Linked brand assets to a Wyoming "Northwest Registered Agent" hub.
Forensic Billing	"MYIQ.COM/EU ST. Julian S MelMT"	Connected the platform to the Maltese payment gateway Mellifera Kartiera Ltd.
Temporal Anchor	site:wyobiz.wyo.gov "MTA Global LLC"	Verified January 22, 2025, as the "First-Use Date" for the trademark.

The AI-Driven Research Stack

To manage the high volume of disparate data, we synthesized an AI-driven research stack using NotebookLM and Gemini to create a comprehensive "Intelligence Map." This process followed a three-step cycle:

1. Automatic Organization: We ingested every search result, MBR filing, and "Application for Authority" into NotebookLM. This created a centralized repository that automatically categorized corporate entities by jurisdiction.
2. Correlation/Dot-Connecting: The AI identified the strategic migration of Envest Research Inc. from New York to Delaware (Claymont) as a calculated asset protection move to exploit Delaware’s corporate secrecy laws.
3. Verification: Gemini functioned as the live research lead, cross-referencing physical addresses against the ICIJ Offshore Leaks Database to verify the legitimacy of various "gatekeepers."

3. The Multi-Jurisdictional Shell Game: Mapping the Three-Layer Shield

The myIQ operation utilizes jurisdictional layering—shifting assets and liabilities between New York, Delaware, Wyoming, and Malta—to shield beneficial owners from consumer protection litigation.

1. The Operational Front (Envest Research Inc.): Based originally in NY but migrated to Delaware, this entity manages the platform and customer support (help@myiq.com). The move to Delaware was a strategic decision to mitigate domestic liability while maintaining a U.S. presence.
2. The IP Shield (MTA GLOBAL LLC): This Wyoming entity serves as a "SEO Shield." The name "MTA Global" was chosen specifically for its "name collision" potential; search results are flooded by the NYC Metropolitan Transportation Authority and whitepapers regarding "Multi-Touch Attribution." This insulates the trademark assets (filed Feb 7, 2025) at the high-density hub of 1309 Coffeen Ave.
3. The Offshore Treasury (Mellifera Kartiera Limited): This is the high-risk payment gateway located at the "Villa Malitah" hub in St. Julian’s, Malta. Referencing the Paradise Papers, we identified this address as a known legacy hub for high-density shell companies.

